transcript: The field marshal looks on and waits for letters addressed to him. We search, but none are to be found. The field marshal grows impatient and sets to work him- self and finds letters from the Emperor to Count T., Prince V., and others. Then he bursts into one of his wild furies and rages at every- one and everything, seizes the letters, opens them, and reads those from the Emperor ad- dressed to others. 'Ah!
